Rolla Schools will be serving FREE MEALS to all USD#217 enrolled students.

Meals will be served on days while school is in regular session during scheduled breakfast and lunch times beginning September 8, 2020 through the end of the 1st semester December 18, 2020, or until federal funding runs out.

Remote learning students are eligible to pick meals up at a prearranged time. Please call the HS office to schedule time. 620-593-4345

Governor's Executive Order 20-16

The governor has now ordered all Kansas to follow the "stay at home" guidelines. However, since school is an "essential service," nothing will change in regards to the school. Our Continuous Learning Plan is still in effect and school personnel can still go to the school. Breakfast and Lunch will still be delivered. It just requires that we stay home from non-essential places. Continuous Learning is still a GO!

post_text: This week's Habit of Success for Rolla Quest is Self-Efficacy. That is believing in yourself and being confident you can do the job, even if it is challenging. It is related to the saying, "If at first you don't succeed, try, try again." If you have self-efficacy, you don't give up when the going gets tough because you know you will eventually succeed if you keep going.

post_text:
This week's Habit of Success for Rolla Quest is empathy and relationship building.

In order to be successful, one needs to know how to build relationships. We do that by being able to relate to others - to "empathize." We can make friends by being friends. When we have those relationships, we are not alone as we face the hardships of life.
